BTTTriggers.BTTPredefinedActionName: Run Apple Script (enter directly as text)
BTTTriggers.BTTInlineAppleScript: if application "iTunes" is running then	tell application "iTunes"		playpause	end tellend if

BTTTriggerConfig.BTTTouchBarAppleScriptString: if application "iTunes" is running then	tell application "iTunes"		if player state is not stopped then			return (get artist of current track) & " - " & (get name of current track)		else			return ""		end if	end tellend ifreturn ""

BTTTriggers.BTTPredefinedActionName: Run Apple Script (enter directly as text)

BTTTriggerConfig.BTTTouchBarAppleScriptString: if application "iTunes" is running then	tell application "iTunes"		if player state is paused then			return ""		else			return "play"		end if	end tellend ifreturn ""

BTTTriggers.BTTPredefinedActionName: Run Apple Script (enter directly as text)
BTTTriggers.BTTInlineAppleScript: if application "iTunes" is running then	tell application "iTunes" to playpauseelse	do shell script "open -a iTunes"end if

BTTTriggerConfig.BTTTouchBarAppleScriptString: if application "iTunes" is running then	tell application "iTunes"		if player state is not stopped then return ""	end tellend ifreturn "play"

BTTTriggers.BTTPredefinedActionName: Open URL / Open URL With Selection

BTTTriggerConfig.BTTTouchBarAppleScriptString: # This script requires two libs. Download them:# https://itunes.apple.com/ru/app/json-helper-for-applescript/id453114608?l=en&mt=12 # https://itunes.apple.com/ru/app/location-helper-for-applescript/id488536386?mt=12 tell application "JSON Helper"	set courses to fetch JSON from "https://alfabank.ru/ext-json/0.2/exchange/cash?offset=0&limit=1&mode=rest"	set usdData to usd of courses		set rec to first item of usdData	set direction to order of rec	set usdVal to value of rec	return "$" & usdVal & directionend tell
